author: app.com
title: Defensive-minded Brick football defeats Colts Neck 24-0
text:
MORE BRICK - The Brick Township football team relied on a shutdown defense and some explosive special teams play in the third quarter from senior Matt Schleifer on Friday night to cruise past Colts Neck, 24-0, at home and stay undefeated.
With a 14-0 lead coming out of halftime, Schleifer immediately put the Green Dragons close to the end zone when he returned a kickoff 43 yards to set up 1st and 10 from the Colts Neck 22-yard line. Three plays later, senior Javion Harris kicked a 25-yard field goal to extend the lead to 17-0.
After a three-and-out from Colts Neck, Schleifer fielded a punt at the Brick 44-yard line, cut across the field to left sideline and turned down field for a 56-yard punt return touchdown that put the Green Dragons up 24-0.
